displayName: City of Ammos in the Desert, Warehouse of the Merchant Guild

parameters:
Commercial Guild Leader Narsa: Our job is to distribute to
stores, so we don't sell to individuals.
Clea: I checked the Magic Academy bulletin board.

Guild Leader Narsa: As expected of Dokusa-san! Without
further ado, let's talk about the main topic.

Guild Leader Narsa: I want you to go to the Mucos region to
search for the missing merchant Eisa and not come back until
you find him.

Clea: I see... Where exactly did he head to in the Mucos
region?
Guild Leader Narsa: Um, well... in the Mucos region...

Priestess Sophia: I'll change the question. Do you have any
idea where he might have gone missing?

Priestess Sophia: For example, he might have been involved
in human trafficking...

Guild Leader Narsa: Th-That's not true! That child, of all
people, would never...!

Clea: It seems like something is being hidden. Can you
please tell us everything honestly?

Guild Leader Narsa: There's a slightly unusual request. I
sent Eisa to the Mucos region's Thieves Market.

Guild Leader Narsa: Even though the requested items have
arrived, the crucial Eisa hasn't returned...

Mage Relm: It's a name that doesn't evoke any sense of
intelligence. It's easy to tell that it's a worthless place.

Thief Nora: I've heard about it from the guild leader! It's
a place where thieves and bandits sell stolen goods!

Clea: Please tell us the location. I want to start the
search from the Thieves Market first.

Guild Leader Narsa: The Thieves Market is located in the
slums of the Mucos region. Eisa is a valuable member of our
guild, please help us.
Clea: Understood, I will definitely bring Eisa back here.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Mucos Region / Slums of the
Defeated Soldiers\c[0]

Commercial Guild Leader Narsa: I apologize for hiding it,
but I want you to definitely help rescue our member, Aisa.

Did you bring Eisa back with you, Chief of the Merchant
Guild?

Clea: I think Eisa-san will wake up soon. There's something
I want to confirm with her.

Chief of the Merchant Guild, Nursa: Eisa... I'm really glad
you're safe.

Merchant Eisa: I have faint memories, and I apologize for
causing trouble to both the guild leader and everyone else.

Clea: I collected the clothes. Can we be sure that this
incident was caused by those clothes?

Merchant Eisa: There is no mistake, it was love at first
sight... It wasn't something as simple as that.

Merchant Eisa: The closest expression would be 'entranced'.
From the moment I saw those clothes, I felt like I was
completely under their control.

Mage Relm: It might be related to the enchanting demon
Namudo. It's possible that it wasn't just a coincidence that
I was in Namudo's cave.

Chief of the Merchant Guild, Nursa: Would you take this
dangerous item? We wouldn't be able to manage it ourselves.

Merchant Eisa: Um... too tall, too short, a little
different...
Merchant Eisa: As I thought, you're the most suitable one!
Priestess Sophia: Oh my, is it me?

Merchant Eisa: I love clothes in the first place, and I feel
like these clothes want to be worn by you.
Mage Relm: ...Are you saying I'm too short!?
Thief Nora: I'm too tall... ugh, it's true though.
Priestess Sophia: Then, I will make use of it.

Chief of the Merchant Guild, Nursa: I truly caused you
trouble. As for the reward, I will make an additional
payment.

Merchant Eisa: Thank you so much. I really like the clothes,
so please come and show them to me.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
実績 悪魔ナムドの礼装

Commercial Guild Leader Narsa: I truly regret it. I won't
accept any more requests for finding strange ingredients.

Merchant Aisa: Hehe, it suits you very well! I think it's
more fitting for you to wear it than for me.

Merchant Aisa: I'll give you something interesting that I
found at the thief market.

Merchant Aisa: Thank you for helping me! Thanks to you, I
can continue doing the job I love.
